title: Gutenberg crashes during opening
body: **Describe the bug** When I click on New post, Gutenberg crashes with 2 errors : `block.js?3527:541 Uncaught TypeError: withAPIData is not a function at eval (block.js?3527:541) at Object. bodyHTML:
Describe the bug
When I click on New post, Gutenberg crashes with 2 errors :

block.js?3527:541 Uncaught TypeError: withAPIData is not a function at eval (block.js?3527:541) at Object.<anonymous> (block.js?ver=3.4.10:331) at __webpack_require__ (block.js?ver=3.4.10:20) at block.js?ver=3.4.10:63 at block.js?ver=3.4.10:66

And

react-dom.min.js?ver=16.6.3:104 TypeError: Cannot read property 'show_ui' of undefined at editor.min.js?ver=9.0.6:55 at i (lodash.min.js?ver=4.17.11:6) at An.filter (lodash.min.js?ver=4.17.11:99) at editor.min.js?ver=9.0.6:55 at ph (react-dom.min.js?ver=16.6.3:97) at eg (react-dom.min.js?ver=16.6.3:125) at fg (react-dom.min.js?ver=16.6.3:126) at wc (react-dom.min.js?ver=16.6.3:138) at fa (react-dom.min.js?ver=16.6.3:137) at gg (react-dom.min.js?ver=16.6.3:135)

I think the second error appears thanks to the first one.

To Reproduce
Steps to reproduce the behavior:

  1. Go to 'Post'
  2. Click on 'New Post'
  3. See error

Screenshots

Desktop (please complete the following information):

  • OS: MAC OS
  • Browser Chrome
  • Version 71.0.3578.98

Additional context

  • I use the last version of gutemberg on wordpress 5.0.2

node.body:
`withAPIData` has been removed from Gutenberg many months ago. It looks like one of your plugins ist still using it, hence the error.

Please try disabling all plugins to see if it works again. If so, try activating plugins again one by one to find the culprit.
